  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n /kind feature\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nAccording to https://github.com/kubernetes/features/issues/284, some volumes(e.g. aws, nfs, ceph) has already supported PV resizing, need to add PV resize support for azure disk\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nPV resize doc is here:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/design-proposals/storage/grow-volume-size.md\r\n\r\nUpdate:\r\nFor azure disk, there is blocking issue: it does not support disk resize on a Running VM. I will try to work on resizing an azure disk which is not in attached state. May dig into more details later. \r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): v1.10.0\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n\r\n/sig azure\r\n/assign",
